commit.message: Update English and German translations
Preferences: add option to prefer ISO-14230 over ISO-15765 if ECU supports both SSM2 protocol variants

CUcontent_sysTests::setup(...): disable actuator tests if protocol is ISO-15765

At least some ISO-15765 ECUs reject actuator start/stop requests for unknown
reasons, which currently results in a communication errors.
As a temporary solution, disable actuator tests for ISO-15765 ECUs.

ControlUnitDialog::handleActuatorTests(...): do not try to stop actuator test if protocol is ISO-15765

At least some ISO-15765 ECUs reject actuator start/stop requests for unknown
reasons, which currently results in a communication errors.
As a temporary solution, don't try to stop actuators during communication start.

ControlUnitDialog: fix+change actuator tests handling on ECU connect

Don't stop actuators for any ECU other than the engine control unit.
It's not clear whether stopping actuators is required for any other
ECUs, so be conservative.
Also don't check test mode state and engine speed if the ECU doesn't
provide this information.
SSMprotocol: assmume test mode state and engine speed are not relevant for actuator tests, if the ECU doesn't provide the corresponding MB / SW

SSMprotocol: add method to find out if the ECU provides engine speed information

The engine speed informaton is used to find out if the engine is running
or not, which is a prerequise for e.g. actuator test start/stop.
Actuator test support for SSM1 ECUs has been added recently and many of them
do not support/use the engine speed information.
So the user needs to know whether the engine state can be retrieved with
isEngineRunning(...) or not.
